snippet: The Dutch Supreme Court narrowed its definition of rape on Tuesday, saying that a “forced tongue kiss” no longer qualifies.
abstract: Dutch Supreme Court narrows its definition of rape, saying that forced tongue kiss no longer qualifies; ruling overturns lower court’s rape conviction of man for forcing his tongue into mouth of woman in hospital restroom and reverses 1998 Supreme Court decision that broadly defined rape as any form of unwanted sexual penetration.
lead_paragraph: The Dutch Supreme Court narrowed its definition of rape on Tuesday, saying that a “forced tongue kiss” no longer qualifies.

headline.main: Netherlands: Forced Kiss Is Not Rape, Supreme Court Rules in Reversal
headline.print_headline: Netherlands: Forced Kiss Is Not Rape, Supreme Court Rules in Reversal
